description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic registered nurse to join our team within Ysbyty Ystrad Fawr. The hospital is a sinle room environemnt that provides nursing care to patients who require a period of stroke rehabilitation and discharge planning. The ward specialises in stroke and neuro rehabilitation and there is excellent multidiscplinary working.&lt;br /&gt;It is expected that the registered nurse will ensure that the patient’s journey is a seamless pathway working closely with the multi disciplinary team and community services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Newly qualified will be given the opportunity to enroll in the Journey of Excellence programme and will be supported to develop their skills and knowledge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CLosing Date: 15th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward Manager Samantha Williams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel 01443 802287&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Samantha.Williams9@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
